items.text: Nice n cheap beehoon at Amoy #01-52! A must have breakfast everyday!
Authentic thai! 01-35. Good and genuine stuff!
Extremely crowded during lunch hours but has a wide variety of food. Try Pepper Bowl on the 2nd floor.
天天熟食-＞赞！
Tian Tian Cooked Food... Nice noodles, price is very cheap!
Tiong bahru porridge👍 especially the sinful fried intestine porridge!!!
Black pepper beef rice from stall no. #02-102 (Pepper bowl) is damn shiok!
Avocado shake a must try
Best coffee and tea at Syed Mohamed Drinks. Cheaper and better than that 2nd floor Coffee Break
Char kaey Teow is nice but a little sweet for my liking. Wanton noodle is not bad
Ban mian ( hand made noodle ) at 02-127. It's is tasty with home cooked favour. No MSG too! A honest bowl of ban mian with chokeful of ingredients.
I recommend dumplings noodle stall no. 01-38. Try n share your view
Good day at level 1 hv v good beef hor fun!
Must try Beef Hor Fun @ Good Day #01-25. Definitely one of the best beef hor fun in Singapore.
Go to 金记drinks corner (#01-29) n try their papa ice lemon tea!! Refreshing n nice!! U wun b able to stop at a cup only!!! Can get hooked!!!
Take exit g from tanjong pagar mrt station
Quench your thirst at Hot & Cold Drink Stall # 01-05
Yau Kee duck rice at 01-32 has the best sauce and chili, always ask for extra chili cause trust me. It's so good!
Awesome hawker fare! Love the Ipoh Hor fun, the wonton mee, fish ball noodles, ytf as and many more!
Best Nasi Lemak! It's the best you can find in Singapore (: $2.50 with 5 Ingredient! Thumbs Up!!
Must try 联合roasted duck, cha siew and roasted chicken!!! @ 01-20
Healthy vegetarian food at #01-14
Awesome coffee at 2nd level,store called coffee break,a daily dose of caffeine that just never gets enough for the coffee lover
The Nasi Padang here super good!
Fried chicken rice from the Sedaap.. Stall is the best! Must try!
I love all da food here. Always make be hard to choose which one to choose!
Intersting store selling Singapore style Ramen..Noodle Story
Economy rice here has pretty good dishes but kinda pricey
Rafi Tea Shop on Level 2. He uses Ceylon Tea for his Tay Tarik.
The uncle from one of the sugar cane stalls here is actually featured in those upskilling ads by WDA! Have you noticed?
I always try the cutlet rice at stall 01-59 and never get sick of it. Auntie super friendly too. Food nice too.
Hor fun with fried fish dumplings at the 2nd level, YUM & affordable for only $3.
AVOID 01-29!They use overnight syrup & 3in1 coffee mix! Whn we q 2 get fruits frm their neighbour stall, auntie frm 01-29 always scold & chase us away! Muz b jealous tt e fruit stall biz alw so gd!
Go to 金记drinks corner (#01-29) in amoy st fd ctr n try their papa ice lemon tea!! Refreshing n nice!! U wun b able to stop at a cup only!!! Can get hooked!!!
Sap Thai is the better Thai stall. Hands down.
Lor Mee, Oyster Pancake, Hainanese Coffee - Must Try!
I love the fish soup here at Han Kee!
try sin kee duck rice. not bad.
Cheap ice lemon tea @ sgd1 at 01-67!
Best beef fried rice & Hor fun! Long Q but super fast!

Try Noodle Story / Authentic Thai (pictured - everything they make is incredible - Thai cook!) or Hong Kee Beef Noodle. Make sure u save a seat w a pack of tissues-it can get packed. Prepare to queue!
Try ZhenJie's Desserts stall at #02-113. Try the peanut filled ah-balling with barley soup base! Delicious~!
Wanton hor fun!!
Teh halia at rafee's on 2nd floor is the best!
Dessert is awesome! Level 2
Basil fried rice all the way!
#01-28 fruit stall, unhealthy and stall owner is extremely rude n atitude.
Beef fried noodles, $3.50, from Sedaaap Noodles, 01-71
Lor Mee, Nasi Lemak, Fish Ball Mee, Piao Ji Fish Soup, Yong Tau Fu (with chee chong fun) - all my favourites, on Level 2
The Nasi lemak stall opens for only half an hour.
Beef Fried Rice #01-25 is my favorite
Probably the only place in singapore where i eat loh mee. Good stuff.
Han Kee must try!
Mince meat noodle @ Ah Ter Teochew Fish Ball Noodle #01-47. Generous portion and taste awesome!!
Yummy Beef Hor Fun at 01-25 but abit salty!
01-04 porridge. Lots of ingredient. Raw fish nice too.
Soon Heng Pork & Fish Porridge (#01-36) serve nice & fresh raw fish...... Yummy
Lor mee!!!
#01-01 Char Koay Teow
The MOST ATTITUDE table cleaners in Singapore.
Try Fried Kway Tiao #01-01! long queue...
Try the kwaychap @ 02-117! It's aweeeesome! :>
Singapore noodles from the noodle story are fantastic.
Fish dumplings hor fun is good! S$3 #02-122
Best fish soup in Singapore at Piao Ji stall 02-100.
Have some Green Curry Chicken and Mango Salad at Authentic Thai, stall #01-35. Simply the best!
Coffee Break at level 2. Yummy roasted almond/hazelnut/caramel coffee at half the price of Starbucks! And the uncle is always so friendly!
So many great stalls, often seating space and often cleaned.
The fish soup at the 2nd story is nice! It's a must try! :D But the attitude of the ladyboss sucks big time. >:(
真姐 dessert at 02-113 really nice! Black sesame paste the best I've tasted so far.
Rong Teochew Fish Porridge #01-12's Fish Soup is one of the greatest in Singapore!!!
Hong Kee Beef Noodle - recipient of Michelin Bib Gourmand 2016 award. Get extra chili - make it spicy! Delicious!! Try to come before 1 or 1:30 - all the best stalls sell out by then!!
5 stars Lo Mee
Mutton chop at 01-63 cost freaking $4.50!!! Serving is so little!!!!!
Xiang Xiang Hainanese chicken rice at #01-02 beats Tian Tian any day (pun intended). Shiok chilli, fragrant rice that's not too oily and really tender tasty chicken. Old couple are such sweethearts
Try the Teh Terik @Raffe's Corner on 2nd level
#01-36 Soon Heng Pork & Fish Porridge Flesh Raw Fish Slice. Must try!!!
Hor fun with fried fish wanton is excellent. 02-122
1st flr there is this chef B western food. Gd n cheap
Must try, corner stall Char Kway Teow near ATM char, upsize more cockles, to die for, noodle story stall not bad, a couple of salad stalls, reasonable priced ask for the sesame dressing yum yum
01-05 stall coffee is good!
Try the beef fried rice and beef hor fun at this stall! They are one of the best you can find in Singapore!
han kee fish soup FTW :)
This beef noodles is not the most popular choice there. Average. Around SGD5-6.

Ah Ter Teochew Fishball Noodles: buy the set with soup - it's not your usual soup! Hoo Kee Bak Chang on first floor is the only bakzhang in SG I've tried that's comparable to my grandma's! Super legit
Soto Warung Wak Ju sedap!!!!
01-47 Ah Ter Teochew Fishball Noodles best in Singapore!
The Wanton Noodle shop on the 2nd flr has the best charsiew!
Penang curry noodle stand is excellent
The pork ribs noodle from chan kee famous prawn noodle and lands stall is awesomeee!!! The meat is soo soft! And try the tomato based sauce, rawks!
Ter's Fishball Noodle
No more POSB ATM here leh. Nearest at TP MRT.
Kway chap @ 02-117 good
Min kee hainanese chicken rice. Pass down from generations and my family just have to come down for our weekly dosage of yummy chicken rice!
Fish soup!
Spoilt for choice hawker centre (Tanjong Pagar Mrt exit G). Avoid lunch time peak hours (12-2pm) and it will be a lot more pleasant. Other than old favorites, can even find Costa Rican cuisine here!
Many delicious food. Hello from Jakarta:)
Why nobody mention the char kuey tiao stall. It's one of the oldest stall around and the char key tiao is very very very yummy. If possible don't 'ta bao'. It just spent taste as good when buy back.
Really good affordable Thai food @ Authentic Thai #01-35. Can't get enough of it.
Hai Kee Famous Porridge is the bomb! Don't forget to add the raw fish.
Warung parsanga's(#01-75) sambal goreng rocks !
#02-100 fish soup super long queue and quite expensive too $7 or $10 bucks for a fish soup. Taste not bad
Almond coffee, Hazelnut coffee is good.
Tai Sun Coffee (#02-121) serves one of the best 80-cents coffees around!
"Zhi Cheng Cooked Food" has very cheap and good 菜贩! 👍🏼
Long queue!
Banana leaf nasi padang- famous fr fried chicken n tahu telor.
The Si Chuan Ban Mian is quite yummy!
Poh Heng Fried Carrot Cake #02-107 yummy $2 only
01-32 traditonal duck rice with cinese herbal soup, awesome
#01-11 hokkien mee is nice loh if u haven't try ^^,
Nasi padang
Roti Prata made with love at Bismillah Muslim Food Stall. One of the best prata & consistently good.
Bak chor mee (minced pork noodles): Yummy BCM meal @ #02-101. Noodles were 'q' (springy), sliced liver was fresh, & sauce was well-balanced with vinegar. Wd eat this again!
ice milo here is cheap and delicious :D
Lor Mee on level 2, up the stairs from POSB ATM.
Great prata on the second floor @ Bismilliah
Tell the uncle at Coffee Break if you don't want sugar/syrup...
Apparently. .there's this long long queue for HAN KEE sliced fish soup. Hmmm...it better be good!
Tian tian cooked food! Cheap breakfast
Try the beef fried rice and beef hor fun at Good Day #01-25. Very delicious and portion is generous. Costs $4
Try min Kee chicken rice at 02-94. Amazing!
Tiong Bahru Hwa Yuen Porridge @ Amoy St Food Centre #02-110
#stervylicious #longtong - best day! Had a great cooling morning over lontong brekky.... Initially when I saw the dish with plain gravy, wasn't impressed... But. Can try for juz $2.50. :)
Unit 02-08 Yuan Chun lor mee, Unit 02-81 nasi lemak (rice run out fast!)
Lots of great food choices for cheap!  Try to avoid lunch hour though... Lineups are crazy!
One local told me that Yuan Chun Famous Lor Mee on the 2nd floor serves the dish loh mee. Come here about lunchtime because it will close in the afternoon.
Try Quan Ji Cook Food when you r here on weekends evenings - cheap & good
plenty of food choices around and dun burn ur pocket
Try the horfun on the second floor. It's a long wait but really worth it! The strawberry juice is the perfect accompaniment.
Wanton mee on 2nd floor is cheap, generous portions and very delicious!
This is one place I don't fancy esp on a extreme hot sunny day. U reach office like u just went for marathon!!
Han Kee fish soup best!!!
New Vietnamese food stall on ground level, near to ATM side. Good Pho, stall managed by husband & wife team. The fried Vietnamese spring rolls are yummy!
The LOR MEE still alright, its A MUST to at BLK 109, BUKIT PURMEI ROAD!
Hazelnut latte is the best!
#stervylicious #meesiam - best day!! Had a 'Fiery' brekky today @ amoy street :)  Can try this dish.....Very unique and definitely worth the try for this stall - nasi padang sederhana / #02-91
02-81 Nasi Lemak is selling the default combo @ $3.
Curry chicken noodle is so nice here.  Do try if visiting here
checkout teochew fish porridge store @01-12. delicious slice fish + home made pork balls porridge !
02-122 Ipoh hor fun 好好吃!!!
Authentic Thai #01-35 nice!!
Beef kway teow at #01-23. Super yummy
As usual, tian tian mee hoon for bf
Try the mee soto at level 1 and teh peng
Piao ji fish soup @ #2 muz try!! B there early at 1130am would b better as the que start coming in ard that timing
Tea Time ~
Banana Leaf Level 2 - Average. Expected better.
Typo error... I mean it doesn't taste as good when buy back.
Nasi lemak. Lor mee. Fishball meepok. Beef kway teow. Soy bean tart. SHIOKNESS!!!!
Bak chor mee 2: Ah Ter 01-14 serves a decent bowl with a variety of ingredients (fishball, sliced fish cakes, pork & liver, stewed mushrooms). Wasn't impressed overall, for all the hype & PR it got.
Overcrowded during lunch hours with white collars. And they use tissue paper to reserve their seats!
Authentic Thai #01-35 is amazing!
Tiong Bahru Hwa Yuen Porridge @#02-110
The queue for fish porridge is LONG. first time here, hope it's nice!
金海熟食！
The lor mee @ #0279/80 changed boss!! New boss bought over the brand/signboard... although long queue but standard dropped.
Better lunch environment compared to Maxwell Food Centre
Hong Kee Beef Noodle at #01-42 is a huge rec. Juicy beef, chewy noodle, hearty broth. Michelin-recognized to boot!
Lor mee, changed boss but same signboard! Price remain but the item is lesser. If u ask for only fried fish and noodles, they charged @ $4 w/o telling you! Consider as 加料 price.
Best fried chicken rice ever!
The wet beef hor fun is yummy.
Must try Sap Thai Food #01-50 for cheap, authentic and yummy Thai food.! Their tom yam soup and Tom yam fried rice is worth the queue!
Join the Q frenzy if you arrive after 12 pm on weekdays!
Ipoh hor fun! Must try!
Try the Masala Tea @ Syed Mohamed Drinks #01-67
02-113 deserts are yummy!!!
Wantan mee: There r 2 WTM stalls facing ea other on 2/F. Wah Kee's dumplings r bigger. Char siew (BBQ pork) slices r thicker too. These make their noodle dish something more substantial to bite in2
Aunt  LiLi is so friendly... Come & try... #01-33
This food centre is super super dirty.
When the clock turn 12pm, no way one could be comfortable there. So early bird catch the good worm ..no long queue, no waiting for table..
01-33 Soya Bean Curd! Superb melts in ur mouth!
The Oyster Pancake Is Definitely The Best You Can Find In Singapore !
free nasi bungkus!
Come early for fish soup at 2nd floor.
Nasi Ayam Goreng from Sedaaap stall is a must-try!
There's a fish soup (lvl 2) is very nice. Long queue during peak hours! :)
Must see the long long q at second floor like maze...lol
Char Kuay Teow
Try the Ah Ter fish ball noodles here. The soup n fishball r yummy
Quan Ji is still the best for 排骨王，鱼头米粉
Food here is decent and affordable considering its location. Many stalls are closed in the evening, and long queue during lunch.
Authentic Thai food at #01-35 :)
First floor char kway tiao is yumz yumz
The fish soup at level 2 is fresh and nice! The meat is thick too!
Lao Shen's avocado juice is awesome!
Fried Guay Tiao 01-01 is great
Lots of coffee varieties, blueberry mocha, double berry mocha hazelnut n much more
Ground level stall Good Day has the best and most economical beef Kway teow. Long line but it goes by really fast!
Best fish soup!
Reasonable  price compares to others.
Lotsa hidden gems here selling at very cheap price.
友记家传鸭饭 Since 1961 $3包括饭，鸭肉，花生，豆干和半颗卤蛋。炒辣椒里头还有酥脆的江鱼仔。赞！
makanan disini mantep-mantep cuy.. pinter-pinter deh ngobrol sama pelayannya biasanya suka dikasih porsi extra hahaha
Nasi Padang at 02-93 has fried fish roe :d

Tiong Bahru Hwa Yuen Porridge #02-110
01-36 porridge stall closed from 25nov to 4dec
Check out Lu Tian Seafood #02-119 zi-cha ...
Try the vietnamese store for their beef noodle soup. Glad to find them here aftwr They moved out from East side. Mon An #01-68
